# Restaurant Insights Report

## 1. Overall Business Performance
Total revenue: KES 500M, Profit: KES 50M, Margin: 10%. 5% YoY growth, stable health.

![Revenue Trends](01_revenue_trends.png)

## 2. Top 3 Profitable Branches
- Nairobi CBD: High volume, efficient costs.
- Westlands: Premium demand.
- Kilimani: Strong location.

![Profit by Branch](03_profit_by_branch.png)

## 3. Bottom 3 (Loss-Making) Branches
- Mombasa: Low demand.
- Nakuru: High staffing.
- Eldoret: Rent pressure.

![Loss Making Branches](10_loss_making_branches.png)

## 4. Key Profit Drivers
AOV and volume drive profits. Cost control essential.

![Profit Drivers](11_profit_drivers.png)

## 5. Cost Inefficiencies
Food costs high; staff in underperformers.

![Cost Breakdown](05_cost_breakdown.png)

## 6. High-Risk Branches
Mombasa, Eldoret: High risk from volatility.

![Risk Distribution](12_risk_distribution.png)

## 7. Recommendations
Optimize costs, target marketing, align staffing.